      "content": "\"unintended consequences\" sounds a lot like a way to brush it under the rug. if you actually look at how this administration has handled the debt and the spending, it looks less like a mistake and more like a strategy to hollow out the middle class power base so we can't push back. it feels like the bankers and these specific politicians are in total lockstep to make sure the wealth just keeps flowing upward. don't you think it's more likely that these economic \"crises\" are actually being managed to favor their specific political agenda and keep everyone else struggling?",
